commit.message:
Apply suggestions from code review

Co-authored-by: Michael <michael-k@users.noreply.github.com>
Fix unittest mock imports that triggered the linter

Drop support for Django 2.1

Reached its EOL on 2019-12-02
https://www.djangoproject.com/download/#supported-versions

Run migrations check only if required version of django is installed

Django master changed the `max_length` of `AbstractUser`'s `first_name`.

See
- https://github.com/django/django/commit/5f8495a40ab1554e81ac845484da890dd390e1d8
- https://github.com/django-guardian/django-guardian/commit/88b8d41ada5de7db2452d67e28955332bf48ecf8
Fix handling of UUIDField for mysql, mariadb and sqlite

Cast object_pk to UUIDField when PK is a UUID

Also, for testing:
- rename NonIntPKModel to CharPKModel to avoid future confusion (UUID is also
non-int)
- add UUIDPKModel
Update link to current django-authority repository

Modify assign_perm shortcut allowing lists

Modify the 'assign_perm' shortcut function to allow lists of objects to
be passed in

Modify BaseObjectPermissionManager allowing lists

Modify BaseObjectPermissionManager allowing lists of objects to be
passed in to its 'bulk_assign_perm' function
Update doc link to latest stable release
Unit test for model inheritance with get_objects_for_user.
